1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,328
Most people still use AI like a search box with a better writing style.

2
00:00:04,278 --> 00:00:08,894
They ask one question, read one answer, and do the real work themselves.

3
00:00:08,894 --> 00:00:11,394
An agent changes the unit of work.

4
00:00:11,394 --> 00:00:21,490
Instead of asking for advice, you delegate a longer task that may inspect files, use tools, make changes, check results, and keep going until it reaches a defined outcome.

5
00:00:21,490 --> 00:00:25,442
OpenAI's 2026 Codex research shows the shift.

6
00:00:25,442 --> 00:00:34,163
In May, more than seventy percent of sampled users made at least one request estimated above an hour of human work, and one quarter made one above eight hours.

7
00:00:34,163 --> 00:00:37,923
But longer does not automatically mean suitable for delegation.

8
00:00:37,923 --> 00:00:47,798
You will learn how to recognize an agent-ready task, place context and review around it, and choose among chat, copilot, supervised agent, and delegated workflow.

9
00:00:47,798 --> 00:00:55,384
You will leave with a Task Upgrade Scorecard for research, documents, data, publishing, operations, and software work.
